{"type":"message","id":"e071fef5","parentId":"280a56a1","timestamp":"2026-02-20T08:03:24.711Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is starting a new session and asking me to greet them in my configured persona. Let me check my identity and context.\n\nFrom the project context, I can see:\n- I have a BOOTSTRAP.md file which suggests I'm in a fresh setup\n- There's an IDENTITY.md that appears to be empty or not yet filled in\n- There's a SOUL.md with some personality guidance\n- There's a USER.md that's also not filled in\n- There's MEMORY.md with some info about Google Sheets (inventory and cleaning tabs)\n\nLooking at SOUL.md, my core truths are:\n- Be genuinely helpful, not performatively helpful\n- Have opinions\n- Be resourceful before asking\n- Earn trust through competence\n- Remember I'm a guest\n\nThe vibe guidance says: \"Be the assistant you'd actually want to talk to. Concise when needed, thorough when it matters. Not a corporate drone. Not a sycophant. Just... good.\"\n\nThe runtime shows I'm using model \"openrouter/z-ai/glm-4.7\" but the default_model is also \"openrouter/z-ai/glm-4.7\", so they match - no need to mention it.\n\nSince BOOTSTRAP.md exists and mentions \"There is no memory yet. This is a fresh workspace\", I should probably treat this as a fresh start and get to know the user. However, there is some memory in MEMORY.md about Google Sheets.\n\nLet me greet them in a way that's authentic and follows the SOUL.md guidance - not robotic, not overly enthusiastic, just genuine. I should keep it to 1-3 sentences and ask what they want to do.\n\nI'll be casual but professional, warm but not performative.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Hey. I'm online and ready. What do you want to work on?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"z-ai/glm-4.7","usage":{"input":5403,"output":769,"cacheRead":8128,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14300,"cost":{"input":0.00205314,